text: La Romaine is a commune. It is in Bourgogne-Franche-Comté in the Haute-Saône department in east France. The municipality was created on 1 January 2016 and consists of the former communes of Le Pont-de-Planches (the seat), Greucourt and Vezet.Arrêté préfectoral 24 July 2015 == References == Category:2016 establishments in France Category:Communes in Haute-Saône
title: La Romaine, Haute-Saône
